#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!meta title=\"Shutting down Tails\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "There are several ways of shutting down Tails, here are a few ones:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* By clicking on the shutdown helper icon located on the top right\n"
"corner of the panel and choosing\n"
"<span class=\\\"guimenuitem\\\">Shutdown Immediately</span> or\n"
"<span class=\\\"guimenuitem\\\">Reboot Immediately</span>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* By removing the device you are running Tails from (USB stick, SD card). Note\n"
"that this method [[doesn't work with DVD|support/known_issues#index11h2]].\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "By pressing the power button of the computer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<div class=\"bug\">\n"
"[[Shutting down Tails by removing the device\n"
"you are running Tails from doesn't work after using the Tails\n"
"USB installer|support/known_issues#index10h2]].\n"
"</div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"When shutting down Tails, RAM is filled out with random data in order to "
"protect Tails user from [[cold boot attacks|doc/advanced_topics/"
"cold_boot_attacks]]."
msgstr ""
